abstract: The extreme cold weather, which prevailed when I wrote last week, has given way, and for the past few days we have had a foretaste of Spring. February, with us, is oftener a gental month than otherwise. From 6 o'clock last night to 5 his morning there was a change of 58  in temperature, the thermometer changing from 38  above to 20  below. abstract: The principal excitement we have on hand just now is the opposition of the Germans and the liquor interest generally to the new Temperance law. They are holding "mass-meetings" all over the State, and on the 14th had a General Convention at the capital, and then and there resolved all sorts of opposition to the obnoxious statute. A permanent organization was formed to fight the law and secure its repeal.
